<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,974]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[399,514,445,470]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1877,1899]" captionTargetBox="[159,1433,198,1851]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Evergestis africalis. A–C) Adult female. A: upperside. B: underside. C: head, in lateral view. D–I) Female genitalia. D: corpus bursae and anterior end of ductus bursae dorso-ventrally. E: main body in lateral view. F, I: colliculum and posterior end of ductus bursae. G, H: signum in lateral (G) and ventral (H) views. The arrows indicate the arising point of ductus seminalis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1247140/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Figs 3D–I</figureCitation>
) (n= 2). Papillae anales connected dorsally and setose; apophyses anteriores about 1.6 times the length of apophyses posteriores, with a triangular process at posterior 0.3; antrum large, funnelshaped, narrowed and sometimes slightly sclerotized anteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[879,994,517,542]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1877,1899]" captionTargetBox="[159,1433,198,1851]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Evergestis africalis. A–C) Adult female. A: upperside. B: underside. C: head, in lateral view. D–I) Female genitalia. D: corpus bursae and anterior end of ductus bursae dorso-ventrally. E: main body in lateral view. F, I: colliculum and posterior end of ductus bursae. G, H: signum in lateral (G) and ventral (H) views. The arrows indicate the arising point of ductus seminalis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1247140/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Figs 3E, I</figureCitation>
); colliculum relatively short (its length nearly 0.4 times the length of antrum or slightly less) and sclerotized; ductus bursae relatively long, slightly more than two times the lengths of corpus bursae, slightly narrowed towards colliculum and somewhat dilated towards corpus bursae, with a lightly granulated surface, ductus bursae deeply folded posteriorly next to the colliculum and sometimes being angled at the junction with colliculum (
<figureCitation box="[791,932,661,686]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1877,1899]" captionTargetBox="[159,1433,198,1851]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Evergestis africalis. A–C) Adult female. A: upperside. B: underside. C: head, in lateral view. D–I) Female genitalia. D: corpus bursae and anterior end of ductus bursae dorso-ventrally. E: main body in lateral view. F, I: colliculum and posterior end of ductus bursae. G, H: signum in lateral (G) and ventral (H) views. The arrows indicate the arising point of ductus seminalis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1247140/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Figs 3E, F, I</figureCitation>
); ductus seminalis arising from the posterior folded end of ductus bursae (
<figureCitation box="[482,626,697,722]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1877,1899]" captionTargetBox="[159,1433,198,1851]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Evergestis africalis. A–C) Adult female. A: upperside. B: underside. C: head, in lateral view. D–I) Female genitalia. D: corpus bursae and anterior end of ductus bursae dorso-ventrally. E: main body in lateral view. F, I: colliculum and posterior end of ductus bursae. G, H: signum in lateral (G) and ventral (H) views. The arrows indicate the arising point of ductus seminalis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1247140/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Figs 3E, F, I</figureCitation>
); corpus bursae nearly globular, with sparsely granulated surface and a dome-shaped area posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[508,598,733,758]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1877,1899]" captionTargetBox="[159,1433,198,1851]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Evergestis africalis. A–C) Adult female. A: upperside. B: underside. C: head, in lateral view. D–I) Female genitalia. D: corpus bursae and anterior end of ductus bursae dorso-ventrally. E: main body in lateral view. F, I: colliculum and posterior end of ductus bursae. G, H: signum in lateral (G) and ventral (H) views. The arrows indicate the arising point of ductus seminalis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1247140/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
) and a clear invagination at signum which is visible before preparing a permanent slide (
<figureCitation box="[349,483,769,794]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1877,1899]" captionTargetBox="[159,1433,198,1851]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Evergestis africalis. A–C) Adult female. A: upperside. B: underside. C: head, in lateral view. D–I) Female genitalia. D: corpus bursae and anterior end of ductus bursae dorso-ventrally. E: main body in lateral view. F, I: colliculum and posterior end of ductus bursae. G, H: signum in lateral (G) and ventral (H) views. The arrows indicate the arising point of ductus seminalis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1247140/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Figs 3D, G</figureCitation>
); signum moderate, nearly one-third of the longitudinal length of corpus bursae or slightly more, with numerous triangular sclerites surrounded by needle-like sclerotized structures (
<figureCitation box="[1291,1423,805,830]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1877,1899]" captionTargetBox="[159,1433,198,1851]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Evergestis africalis. A–C) Adult female. A: upperside. B: underside. C: head, in lateral view. D–I) Female genitalia. D: corpus bursae and anterior end of ductus bursae dorso-ventrally. E: main body in lateral view. F, I: colliculum and posterior end of ductus bursae. G, H: signum in lateral (G) and ventral (H) views. The arrows indicate the arising point of ductus seminalis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1247140/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Figs 3G, H</figureCitation>
); length of the sternite VII 2.6 times the length of sternite VIII.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,974]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,319,877,902]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Variation.</emphasis>
In the examined females, ground color variation was observed in the forewing, being buffish-cream to dirty-cream, and the post-median line was paler in the buffish-cream ground color.
</paragraph>
